<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1322,1513,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,464,1513,1539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[478,538,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Male</emphasis>
: Total length 4.08 mm (SD = 0.31, n = 10), prosoma 2.03 mm (SD = 0.14, n = 10) long, 1.58 mm (SD = 0.14, n = 10) wide. 
<emphasis box="[943,1026,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Colour</emphasis>
: Prosoma and chelicerae light brown, legs yellow. Sternum yellow with thin brown margin. Opisthosoma dorsally sepia brown, ventrally pale. 
<emphasis box="[595,650,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Palp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[665,787,1633,1659]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1371,1395]" captionTargetBox="[302,1287,861,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[280,1306,849,1361]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Zodarion bosmansi sp. n. 9 male palp, ventral view. 10 male palp, retrolateral view. 11 epigyne, ventral view. 12 vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048942" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048942/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Figs 9–10</figureCitation>
): tibial apophysis long and gently curved, terminally truncate. Retinaculum (unnaturally expanded) with distal sharp tooth, embolus hooked, distal tegular apophysis broad and flattened.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1322,1513,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis box="[312,400,1753,1778]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Female</emphasis>
. Total length 4.84 mm (SD = 0.45, n = 10), prosoma 2.33 mm (SD = 0.13, n = 10) long, 1.71 mm (SD = 0.15, n = 10) wide. 
<emphasis box="[811,894,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Colour</emphasis>
: as in males. 
<emphasis box="[1059,1155,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Epigyne</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1172,1309,1793,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="5.[264,382,1371,1395]" captionTargetBox="[302,1287,861,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-345@5.[280,1306,849,1361]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Zodarion bosmansi sp. n. 9 male palp, ventral view. 10 male palp, retrolateral view. 11 epigyne, ventral view. 12 vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048942" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048942/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Figs 11–12</figureCitation>
): median plate wider than long, anterior margin well marked with paired sclerotised lips. Openings at lateral margins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
